'''Arda Unmarred''' ([[Valarin|Val]]. '''''Aþāraphelūn Amanaišal''''',<ref>{{WJ|AD1}}, p. 401</ref> [[Quenya|Q]]. '''''Arda Alahasta'''''<ref>{{MR|P3II4}}, p. 254</ref> or '''''Arda Vanya'''''<ref>{{PE|17}}, p. 150</ref>) is a concept in [[Elves|Elvish]] religion and philosophy. It refers to [[Arda]] (the world) as it existed in a perfect state following its creation, as opposed to '''[[Arda Marred]]''', the flawed world as it currently exists. Arda Unmarred was a world not yet tainted by the evil of [[Morgoth]]. This reflects the original intention of the creator, [[Eru Ilúvatar]], and his servants the [[Ainur]].

The Elves lament the spiritual and physical corruption of Arda. They live in [[Estel|hope]] that one day this damage will be undone and the world will be purged of all evil, restoring it to a paradise state.

